dct_description_sm: This line data layer represents airport runways in Wisconsin in 1996. The dataset was originally created by the Bureau of Transportation Statistics and published by the Legislative Technology Services Bureau in 2000.[This data layer is a line shapefile of the public-use runways (both publicly and privately owned) within the state of Wisconsin as of 1996. The original data set was a comprehensive geographic database of runways in the United States containing information on the physical characteristics of the runways. The original database includes runways in all 50 states as well as US territories. It is referenced to the Wisconsin Transverse Mercator (WTM) projection system, North American Datum 1983, with the 1991 adjustment (NAD83/91).]
